() Tj
T*
(6. Useful Operations) Tj
T*
(Restart service: sudo systemctl restart media-controller.service) Tj
T*
(Check status:    sudo systemctl status media-controller.service) Tj
T*
(View service log: sudo journalctl -u media-controller.service -n 100 --no-pager) Tj
T*
(Playback logs: tail -n 100 slideshow.err.log) Tj
T*
(               tail -n 100 slideshow.out.log) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. Networking Notes) Tj
T*
(For mobile access, web app must bind to 0.0.0.0 \(already configured\).) Tj
T*
(If running in VM, use Bridged network mode. NAT IP \(10.0.2.x\) is usually not reachable from) Tj
T*
(phone.) Tj
T*
(Phone and Raspberry Pi must be on the same Wi-Fi/network.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8. Known Behavior) Tj
T*
(A small media transition delay can still occur on lower Raspberry Pi hardware, especially while) Tj
T*
(switching players.) Tj
T*
(Use lower-resolution videos \(e.g., 720p H.264\) for smoother startup and transitions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(9. Maintenance Checklist) Tj
T*
(Keep Python packages updated in virtual environment.) Tj
T*
(Monitor disk usage for photos/videos folders.) Tj
T*
(Backup config.json and media folders regularly.) Tj
T*
(Test START/STOP flow after OS updates.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
